I needed that as a food critic. So, all in all, almost everything hit the right spot and took me on Indian streets for a moment. We were served by Lay and he was super friendly and kind. My wife has been trying to get me to go to Eggoholic for months but I was afraid of the all-egg concept. I gave up meat for the month of January as a New Years resolution and finally made the trip here. And I have to admit it’s blowing my mind. By far the best Indian food Ive had in Chicago, and I go to Devon street quite often. I’m excited to tell people about this place which has great customer service on top of phenomenally mind blowing flavors. I recommend it to all that love curry, paneers, and Indian spices. I should have come here as a meat eater as they also have Chicken dishes as well which I imagine is as good as what I e had so far. Definitely coming back next weekend.

This was my very first time eating an Indian meal and drinking an Indian beverage. I ordered the Chatpata Anda Sandwich (sriracha flavored) and a Sweet Lassi recommended by the pleasant and helpful hostess, Sayali.  The sandwich was similar to a grilled cheese club but with an Indian flair of ingredients and flavor, served w/ a side of chips and a side condiment which I dipped my sandwich in. The beverage looked like frothy milk but tasted more like yogurt and slightly orchata.  My plan was to eat half my sandwich and save half for my lunch break later. Needless to say nothing was left. I finished the soft and crusty sandwich in minutes and sipped the beverage while watching an Indian film on one of three screens over the bar and listening to Indian music through the speakers above.  What a pleasant first experience! Thank you.

This is conceivably the best Indian food I’ve had in the city. I love Indian and have lived in the city for most of my life (ventured to Devon many times etc.) Although the idea of egg-only dishes may seem a little odd, you won’t even think of it once you start eating. The textures are varied and unexpected. And the flavors are incredible. I love the Cheese Katori, Garlic Half Fry (ask for full fry version), Surti Gotalo, any of the sandwiches (which is like a club sandwich with Indian flavored protein). The service is also always kind and friendly. Jinen has taken care of us on numerous occasions and is the best. Go now.

I gave this place a second chance and it lived up to its name! Egg-O-Holic is an Indian restaurant specializing in egg dishes but they do have vegetarian and chicken options as well. I tried their chicken masala sandwich, chicken holic kebab plate and their egg lachko. The food was delicious, flavorful and spicy. But mind that the food is on the oily/buttery side, so of course it tastes great. They serve their dishes in cheaper plastics, so it really is like a fast food place. I just wish they served their curry dishes in bowls instead of plates.

I had to give them my email address to get a receipt for a business dinner, since they have no option for a printed receipt.  I started getting spam from them the very next day through a scummy 3rd party ad company.  "Removing" myself from the list does nothing, since the 3rd party terms of service "allows" them to re-subscribe me to any other lists I might be interested in.  (They also promise to keep my financial information,  name, email address, and any other information they can find about me, online and otherwise, forever, to be shared with anyone they want.
